<subSubSection id="301272D190341CFE25F5AD18BDD514FA" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D298B6017B28B28C425A7BC529583DDD" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A586BF5B0C866615941C571ECC112D50" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
The genital morphology of male 
<taxonomicName id="422EEDA2A4C8946DBCF161A7E5F04756" genus="S." lsidName="S. recherchensis" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="recherchensis">
<emphasis id="78C425F598CE6ADC190DEE970AD22A1A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. recherchensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. is most similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4EB1894C9D18FAFB983BC4449469DB8F" genus="S." lsidName="S. fuliginata" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="fuliginata">
<emphasis id="FE033996333D7660866AD74D7B668295" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. fuliginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov.; however, 
<taxonomicName id="F47AF108AB03F3D9F7A5DFCBCECCC6F6" genus="S." lsidName="S. recherchensis" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="recherchensis">
<emphasis id="A94E72ECD120D4692AD8D05425A83938" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. recherchensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. males can be distinguished by the comparatively shorter median apophysis and the distinct basal spine-like prong on the terminal apophysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8343DEFA0D4653D74F92C903C1CBE0BF" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Salsa fuliginata (L. Koch, 1872), comb. nov., male (MV K- 14867 (CVIC 1163 )) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686605" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">6C</figureCitation>
vs. Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6CA71F331E6DA72F2C2C7279EE1FD166" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17C</figureCitation>
). The epigyne of female 
<taxonomicName id="115B626ACF3DA2351A02FD448E4E2CAA" genus="S." lsidName="S. recherchensis" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="recherchensis">
<emphasis id="37927C661DF257C650E4941CA28DF11A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. recherchensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. is most similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="E9AA8E95223A2A0066C8F5AD915B80A8" genus="S." lsidName="S. fuliginata" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="fuliginata">
<emphasis id="A66B82944F170F0D9059DAA0BAAC4049" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. fuliginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. However, in ventral view, the epigyne plate of 
<taxonomicName id="753D8F5B28F2CE4DCC295047F2D757E6" genus="S." lsidName="S. fuliginata" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="fuliginata">
<emphasis id="C7BF5A2BE97ECF9C4988F8F98D6C96CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. fuliginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. is inconspicuous (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="344AA4BA07681A06B0B807F0D9243BBA" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Salsa fuliginata (L. Koch, 1872), comb. nov., female (MV K- 14863 (CVIC 1173 )) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, postero-ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view F epigyne in situ, ventral view (MV K- 4866). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686606" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">7F</figureCitation>
), whereas it is pronounced in 
<taxonomicName id="F9FE2A87042F0FCE0F50BF44D30648FB" genus="S." lsidName="S. recherchensis" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="recherchensis">
<emphasis id="198EDAE13BF66C572F98FFB1BA33320D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. recherchensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B8F6F4B5398CF8F7CFA96B4057D9D586" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., female (WAM T 77362) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view F variation of epigyne, ventral view (WAM 92 / 2120) G variation of epigyne, lateral view (WAM 92 / 2120). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686617" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">18C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CB1E107B83E2F1BE0CA5557EB4C1BBEB" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="redescription">
<paragraph id="64412D328C665C06B0F34DE2A6F18D3F" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DF2C0DAA2772B0A9B8CC221D53B79F83" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="81E9C57EC8766CA98CED4FC90A92B9A0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Male</emphasis>
(based on WAM T73696). Total length 5.1. Carapace 2.9 long, 2.4 wide, brown, paler in cephalic area and with yellowish setae throughout (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2CD6CBED00851A2C2EAA9A4F6B95F44E" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.18, ALE 0.14, PME 0.09, PLE 0.09; row of eyes: AME 0.50, PME 0.43, PLE 1.39. Chelicerae brown; with four promarginal teeth (second basal and apical largest) and three retromarginal teeth (basal largest). Legs brown, femora basally yellow-brown, except in leg I (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="18D3AD277A617794393D41B9691B709B" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17A, B</figureCitation>
). Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 4.2 + 1.6 + 3.2 + 3.3 + 1.0 = 13.3, II - 3.4 + 1.3 + 2.2 + 2.8 + 1.0 = 10.7, III - 2.2 + 0.9 + 1.1 + 1.4 + 0.7 = 6.3, IV - 3.2 + 1.1 + 2.2 + 2.5 + 0.9 = 10.0. Labium 0.34 long, 0.56 wide, brown; endites orange-brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3F2957282E648A3904A838E2F99DC7B1" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 1.5 long, 1.0 wide, brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E332B3B1C7C0D890A7CC717641F229B1" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 2.3 long, 2.1 wide, dorsum with dark grey, irregular folium on a beige background, laterally olive-grey (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FAF43CF01BE3FDABF08ED4AD1B413BD5" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17A</figureCitation>
); venter olive-grey, laterally with two elongate, curved longitudinal bands (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E1307EEB2418466AAA18C7C21B71E82C" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + cymbium = total length): 0.6 + 0.2 + 0.15 + 0.8 = 1.75; paracymbium stout and slightly curved apically (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D09803BE20900ED9B2A62B87B1E57BA6" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17D</figureCitation>
); median apophysis short with thick rounded tip, numerous small teeth-like tubercles inside basal arch (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="252BFD426B832473735F9E9A7DC1A138" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17C</figureCitation>
); conductor lobe short (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="45EE1AAA0A128858462C6A12BE18034C" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17C</figureCitation>
); terminal apophysis conspicuous, sub-rectangular and bearing spine-like basal prong (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="66805D23380B8AB43698E8C09FAE9EE1" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17C</figureCitation>
); conductor slightly folding over itself, broadly lapped and heavily sclerotised (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="053F6AA602C55ED75415693E373E1DF0" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17C, D</figureCitation>
); embolus short (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="27F6D25686B8F5C07D48837E2A68E0FC" captionStart="Figure 17" captionStartId="F17" captionText="Figure 17. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., male (WAM T 77696) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686616" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">17C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
