<paragraph id="80B3E097CC81376E5D94B01B65A332F5" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="314EDC7996EAF815A586ECCF841F96A0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Female</emphasis>
(based on WAM T77362): Total length 8.0. Carapace 3.7 long, 2.7 wide; similar to male but slightly darker and more setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9D4727D7C402CCF3FA2DAD750EEC2D50" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., female (WAM T 77362) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view F variation of epigyne, ventral view (WAM 92 / 2120) G variation of epigyne, lateral view (WAM 92 / 2120). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686617" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">18A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.20, ALE 0.18, PME 0.13, PLE 0.11; row of eyes: AME 0.52, PME 0.47, PLE 1.76. Chelicerae pale brown, four promarginal teeth (apical and second basal largest) and three retromarginal teeth (basal largest). Legs pale brown mottled in dark (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F94BD1E61073EBFFCDF00597F0CD323D" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., female (WAM T 77362) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view F variation of epigyne, ventral view (WAM 92 / 2120) G variation of epigyne, lateral view (WAM 92 / 2120). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686617" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">18A, B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + tarsus = total length): 0.9 + 0.5 + 0.7 + 1.1 = 3.2. Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 3.4 + 1.5 + 2.7 + 2.9 + 1.1 = 11.6, II - 2.8 + 1.3 + 2.3 + 2.4 + 1.0 = 9.8, III - 2.0 + 1.0 + 1.3 + 1.3 + 0.7 = 6.3, IV - 3.0 + 1.2 + 2.0 + 2.2 + 0.8 = 9.2. Labium 0.34 long, 0.72 wide, dark brown; endites dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="29FD262CF3E4EC917F8B886ABB52983F" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., female (WAM T 77362) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view F variation of epigyne, ventral view (WAM 92 / 2120) G variation of epigyne, lateral view (WAM 92 / 2120). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686617" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">18B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 1.5 long, 1.4 wide, dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0B8CEA8B864499C14DFADC50A0D64F4B" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., female (WAM T 77362) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view F variation of epigyne, ventral view (WAM 92 / 2120) G variation of epigyne, lateral view (WAM 92 / 2120). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686617" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">18B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 5.1 long, 4.7 wide; folium pattern as in male, but more distinct (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F787D97EF3ADED16979C2CD0DF976F65" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., female (WAM T 77362) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view F variation of epigyne, ventral view (WAM 92 / 2120) G variation of epigyne, lateral view (WAM 92 / 2120). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686617" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">18A, B</figureCitation>
). Epigyne base slightly longer than wide; atrium heart-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5D1DD126CE9FA66102508CD9E040CC26" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., female (WAM T 77362) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view F variation of epigyne, ventral view (WAM 92 / 2120) G variation of epigyne, lateral view (WAM 92 / 2120). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686617" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">18C</figureCitation>
); central division ca. as wide as the epigyne base, slightly narrowing dorsally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CD3ED422FFB0D4284BB003606DA2F63F" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., female (WAM T 77362) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view F variation of epigyne, ventral view (WAM 92 / 2120) G variation of epigyne, lateral view (WAM 92 / 2120). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686617" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">18E</figureCitation>
); spermathecae spherical (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D169E56828DE060989C96CA8B6743A91" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Salsa gen. nov. female epigynes, cleared posterior view A S. fuliginata (L. Koch, 1872), comb. nov. (CVIC 173) B S. brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov. (AM KS. 131087) C S. canalae comb. nov. Berland, 1924, comb. nov. (WAM T 75921) D S. recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov. (WAM T 77362) E S. rueda sp. nov. F S. tartara sp. nov. (AM KS. 7061). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686604" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">5D</figureCitation>
); scape (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4112FC86122FD0E895DD92D03D54C0D1" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov., female (WAM T 77362) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C epigyne, ventral view D epigyne, lateral view E epigyne, posterior view F variation of epigyne, ventral view (WAM 92 / 2120) G variation of epigyne, lateral view (WAM 92 / 2120). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-E)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686617" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">18F, G</figureCitation>
.) (WAM 90/2120) broadest at base, tapering, curved in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8ED8CC071C4BC2DD3413E068766885B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="variation">
<paragraph id="B418D7E8C52FE3354C30D833954E8F42" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F67E6653023460F030AB0D56F9446394" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Only a single male was measured for this study; female total length 4.5-8.0 (
<emphasis id="C0A2290D9201209982BBAF96B8B17D55" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">n</emphasis>
= 6). The colour variation in this species is very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="A6F2EBFD437B47D7C16CE5E49ED146C8" genus="S." lsidName="S. fuliginata" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="fuliginata">
<emphasis id="2BE31A5170277062BB38DF64087B32C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. fuliginata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="69B3CF220FC700D0F0566B8DF151EF22" genus="S." lsidName="S. brisbanae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="217C6B2AEEB2D7C7C4BD825BD3EBDC36" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. with abdominal shades of beige to reddish brown and more or less conspicuous folium pattern. Of the six females measured for this study, all but one had their scapes broken off.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B934B1084C43560D6CBD545BB70A1C6A" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="life history and habitat preferences">
<paragraph id="1D76FC8CAEA65E05A5C6D1B5528C101A" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Life history and habitat preferences.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="920AFE46C4ADCF573CEC85DA2340CC71" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
All specimens were collected between October and May, with peak collection numbers in November and January. There is not much information about habitat preferences of 
<taxonomicName id="6A66EE9F7C13FFA4ED84DD0286B95496" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Main" baseAuthorityYear="1954" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa recherchensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recherchensis">
<emphasis id="E6D610204AB0261DA2780907E161CE1C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa recherchensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov., but they seem to be more common in lower vegetation layers based on descriptions on specimen labels, which include &quot;web in garden&quot;, &quot;understorey Karri forest&quot;, 
<normalizedToken id="08F9CD3077C477F1180B9D6F9ABFB034" originalValue="“bushes”">&quot;bushes&quot;</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="77C56D3B21FA804874376E5451EED783" originalValue="“granite”">&quot;granite&quot;</normalizedToken>
, &quot;between limestone&quot;, and 
<normalizedToken id="3AA29CBC58E295F2837C2261E583F27A" originalValue="“camp”">&quot;camp&quot;</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DE6A780F3ED7AC53EDB528D8DFC0DC47" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F0B564DAAC47ECA863B37B9381103B27" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3BF4A96CB6193C7306555FA0B38E5D1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName id="C8D5530FC657EAC8E5F642C0EF9FEF45" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Main" baseAuthorityYear="1954" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa recherchensis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="recherchensis">
<emphasis id="B03D9AC01683386B50D3CD06623AFB94" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa recherchensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. is the only species of the genus found in Western Australia, although its range extends into southern South Australia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4157EEBC9E48B3025EA14C2CB8B13EEA" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Distribution records of Salsa brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov. and Salsa recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov. in Australia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686610" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
